A vintage-style illustration of a freshly squeezed orange being transformed into mechanical gears and circuit components, with orange juice droplets morphing into tiny glowing data streams. The scene is set on a weathered wooden workbench with antique brass tools scattered around. Warm amber and copper tones dominate, with deep shadows creating dramatic contrast. The orange peel curls elegantly to one side while delicate clockwork mechanisms emerge from the fruit's center, suggesting organic creativity merging with engineering precision. Soft, diffused lighting from an unseen window casts long shadows, evoking a 1940s workshop aesthetic with subtle sepia undertones and film grain texture.
